Dating: RAMESSES II/USERMAATRE-SETEPENRE (not before); 19TH DYNASTY ?; NEW KINGDOM (not after)
Name: Plaque in the shape of a cartouche
Description: This plaquette of terracotta, which was part of the Hilton Price collection, constitutes in reality a cartouche containing the "Son of Re" name of Ramesses II. The exact function of the piece is not known with certainty: it could be  an element of inlay in an architectural decoration (?).
